  "title": "Error serializing metadata on SSR",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\n\r\nWhen serializing results on the server side an error is thrown because the metadata array contains an object where one of the fields is a function. \r\n\r\n`resultsState.metadata[0].items[0].value` is a function and therefore cannot be serialized. I'm not sure if I have misconfigured something or if I've encountered a bug. \r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n\r\n1. Go to [codesandbox](https://codesandbox.io/s/cool-matsumoto-3p4w6?file=/app/pages/search.tsx) and navigate to the `/search` path\r\n2. Load the page\r\n3. Look at the error\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\n\r\nI'm able to serialize the resultsState on the server side. I wouldn't expect that call to ever return an object with a function inside of it. \r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n\r\n - OS: mac\r\n - Browser: chrome (but not really applicable here)\r\n - Version 6.10.3\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\nI'm trying to build a search page for an app I'm creating that is built with blitzjs (a fullstack framework that runs on top of nextjs). I've been trying to adapt the next js example for react-instant search but keep running into errors. \r\n",
